To express the idea that there are no gods, we can define an empty, null object in the real world. It is possible, as you suggested, to use the nullity operator to create an empty object. For example: 

```
class emptyObject : object {
    void print() {
        System.out.println("emptyObject!");
    }
}

```

Now the type of this object would be: `emptyObject` and would be an `EmptyObject`.
